{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NZau2sFqnqG36hrgdX7bxB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The auth-checker uses HTTP (not HTTPS) to connect to ES. But ES has HTTPS enabled. So either the auth-checker is broken by design (the probe will fail because ES won't respond on HTTP), or there's something else going on.\n\nWait, let me re-read the auth-checker probe:\n```\ncurl -s --max-time 5 -u elastic:${ELASTIC_PASSWORD} \\\n  http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_security/_authenticate \\\n  | grep -q '\"username\":\"elastic\"'\n```\n\nThis uses HTTP, but ES has SSL enabled. Unless... ES also listens on HTTP? Let me check if there's a port 9200 without SSL.\nWith `xpack.security.http.ssl.enabled: true`, ES should only accept HTTPS on 9200, so the HTTP probe would fail. But the task says the auth-checker should become healthy after the rotation, which makes me wonder if there's a special configuration or if I'm missing something about how the service is set up.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":775,"cache_read_input_tokens":31906,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":775},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"172ce35c-29a4-4b84-ac42-0007ac6c7e5c","uuid":"6b02000e-4569-461b-876c-216c75fcbb8a","request_id":"req_011CcgHejpyEMbhKE1iEmzcx"}
