he password again during initialization. Let me check how Elasticsearch handles this in its startup sequence.\n\nIn Elasticsearch 8.x, the Docker entrypoint only calls `elasticsearch-reset-password` during initial setup when the security realm hasn't been initialized yet. Since the StatefulSet uses persistent volumes for data, the security configuration persists across restarts, so the password won't be reset again just because the environment variable changed. This means my approach is sound: I can rotate the password via the API first, then update the secret for future authentications, and the restart will preserve the new password. I'm realizing the ES 8.x Docker image might actually reapply the `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` environment variable on every restart, which would reset the password back to the old value if I restart before updating the secret. So I need to flip the order: update the secret to the new password first, then restart ES so it picks up the new value from the environment variable.\n\nLet me verify this assumption by checking the actual startup scripts in an ES pod to confirm how the password initialization works.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":626,"cache_read_input_tokens":39701,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":626},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"172ce35c-29a4-4b84-ac42-0007ac6c7e5c","uuid":"363cd455-8c50-4558-836e-7532fedb81b3","request_id":"req_011CcgHjKi2iuQKu3c73CQXr"}
