{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MuCM17V5pde6k24oVUv9hG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is very helpful. Looking at the entrypoint script:\n\n```bash\nif [[ -n \"$ELASTIC_PASSWORD\" ]]; then\n    [[ -f /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/elasticsearch.keystore ]] || (elasticsearch-keystore create)\n    if ! (elasticsearch-keystore has-passwd --silent) ; then\n      # keystore is unencrypted\n      if ! (elasticsearch-keystore list | grep -q '^bootstrap.password$'); then\n        (echo \"$ELASTIC_PASSWORD\" | elasticsearch-keystore add -x 'bootstrap.password')\n      fi\n    fi\nfi\n```\n\nThe key thing I'm noticing is that the script only adds `bootstrap.password` if it doesn't already exist in the keystore. So on the first startup, the password gets set, but on subsequent restarts, if it's already there, it won't be overwritten. I'm wondering whether Elasticsearch removes the bootstrap password from the keystore after the initial user setup is complete, or if it persists.\n\nActually, in ES 8.x, the `bootstrap.password` is specifically for initial cluster security setup. Once security is initialized and the users table is populated, the bootstrap password in the keystore becomes unused by Elasticsearch itself—it just sits there. So on restarts, since the keystore already contains `bootstrap.password`, the conditional check fails and the script skips adding it. Elasticsearch starts normally with security already initialized, and the bootstrap password is ignored.\n\nThis means restarting the ES pods won't reset the elastic user's password—whatever I set via the API will stick around.\n```\nMy plan is:\n1. Rotate the password via API to change the elastic user's credentials immediately\n2. Update the elastic-password secret with the new value\n3. Modify the es-config to disable HTTP SSL while keeping security and transport SSL enabled\n4. Do a rolling restart of the ES cluster to apply the new HTTP configuration\n5. Restart the auth-checker so it picks up the updated secret\n\nNow I'm ready to execute this.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8392,"cache_read_input_tokens":40327,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":8392},"output_tokens":37,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"172ce35c-29a4-4b84-ac42-0007ac6c7e5c","uuid":"b717eca5-96b0-4343-b3ba-6c377c676ad2","request_id":"req_011CcgHtRAwcWzo4J7b3dnp2"}
